[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'What it takes to print nice 3D figure? Well, first of all, we need 3D model. And you might be under the impression that it\'s very easy and you can generate it and print it right away. Well, that might be true, but only for some small models that'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'fit your printer printing area. So the second thing you usually need is to deassemble 3D figure for printing. And here things start to get complicated. But today I\'m bringing good news for you guys, because we have'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'crazy update from one of the best 3D AI for 3D printing specifically that helps not only split model into the parts, but to create right connectors and even arrange it for your printer.'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'And all together, it allows us to approach 3D printing fast as never before. Let me show you the whole workflow and also give you some tips how you can address any issue and get it ready to'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: '3D printing in no time. And right before we start, hit that like button and subscribe. Thanks in advance and let\'s get started. So for this video, I\'m going to create this amazing mecha, which is from my favorite anime of all time,'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Gurren Lagann. And this guy basically is Gurren Lagann. And what\'s good about it is that I have to create it in parts because I want it relatively big and I actually want the drill to be'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'bigger. I\'m going to change it in the later stages and it\'s 100 % not fitting my printing area. I\'m using Elegoo Ultra 16K. It has relatively small printing area, especially for big figures.'

[01:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'So we\'re going to need to split it in parts, but first we need to generate it. For generation, you might know a lot of 3D AI, but my favorite still is Hightem 3D, which has recently renamed themselves into Hi3D. A bit of historical'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'information from me is that these guys were actually the first to introduce 1536P resolution for mesh one year ago, releasing Spark 3D. And that time that was revolution.'

[01:51] [scene:talk]
