[02:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'So I already prepared all my reference and we\'re going to use Multiview. Here we have some image enhancement and remove backgrounds, use them on demand. That works pretty fine, but I used to prepare my reference to'

[02:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'get 100% of control. I do have separate video about references. If you struggle with them, take a look. For the model type, of course we go with quality because we\'re going to split it and I want each part to have as'

[02:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'much details, but we do not need really a texture. So we\'re going to go for geometry, right? For us, for 3D printing, that\'s not really needed. License, private and in advanced options, we can pretty much keep everything as is.'

[02:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'I will only uncheck UV unwrap since again, we do not do texturing and that\'s pretty much it. So I did few generations and here are some options. And also Hi3D offers free retries up to'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'three times, 100% use them. Generative AI is generative. So for something complex, you might want to do free retries. Then here are the options that you get, split parts, texture edit, but we don\'t really'

[03:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'need that. So you can download it here or you can keep it here and we need to go to next feature. The next feature and the reason of this video is split to print. So we\'re going to go here and there are two modes.'

[03:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'The first one is character and there are presets. You can select the model you created here. If you prefer generation and union, triple, you can bring it here and process, which is great, but my character'

[03:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'is a bit more complex than this and I definitely want to split more parts. So let\'s find my character in upload. Okay. The model is selected. Now I\'m going to choose professional mode. There is a tutorial'

[03:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'that will help. And for segmentation, I\'m going to go with low. Actually, low and medium is more than enough for printing because high really splits into a lot of parts. And then we\'re going to generate mask.'

[03:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'So the mask is stepped before splitting into the parts so you can confirm amounts of parts. So it looks like this quite simple. And what do we need to do here is that I want to first separate the drill and also the'

[04:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'shields on the shoulders. Well, not shoulders, but arms really, we also going to need to separate. So there are a bunch of tools here like LASO, splits and merge. Here in the instruction, you can see what'

[04:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'they does. Basically LASO helps to add new parts like this. Split allow you to select one part that is already separated and split it like this. And merge is to select two parts and'

[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'merge them by pressing the confirm. In my case, I just need to split parts because mostly it\'s all good. So we\'re going to need to split the drill and then we\'re going to need to split shields on the arms.'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'If you did something wrong, you can always press mask record and revert. Well, that\'s pretty much it. We do have all the parts and we\'re ready to hit the generate. And here we go. Here\'s the result. There is a explode'

[04:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'mode and we can review the result. And overall, the amount of parts is exactly as in. There are a few things that we need to address here is that there are some floating pieces that are separated with mask.'

[05:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'But what we\'re going to need to do is just select them and join them with the object that they belong. So let\'s say in my case, it will be the object like this. And don\'t worry about holes.'

[05:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'We\'re going to fill them because they\'re a special function. First, we\'re going to merge regions and make sure we do not have floating stuff left. Okay, all done. And now we have everything fine. No floating stuff, just the pieces that we'

[05:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'need. And we can actually hit the fill face button that will actually cap holes in a very nice and smooth way. You can preview the results. In my case, everything is fine. And we finally can'

[05:42] [scene:talk]
