AUDIO: 'Now, this also can help to smooth some creases like this. My second favorite brush is definitely grab or elastic wrap. There are both brushes that are so cool to use. Basically, it\'s like working'

[10:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'with clay. Let\'s say I want to adjust the lines here on the drill and I just select the right size. Again, you can select the right size here in radius, or you can press F hot key and control the'

[10:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'size. And as simple as this, I can easily adjust the shape. There\'s another brush called pinch that is made perfectly for these cases that will help to pinch and make these holes more narrow.'

[10:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'And one more cool, cool brush that I want to show you called pose. And yeah, you might guess it helped to pose some stuff. It understands the shape of the object. And let\'s say I'

[10:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'want to move the arm a little bit to the side and here I can see it draw the line and we can easily move it like this. Really helpful. Sometimes when you work in sculpting mode, you might face the situation when there are some'

[11:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'stuff that you can not remove or smooth, or you can not make holes or draw on the mesh. Well, that happens because the mesh might be a limited by the polygons. And if we go to the polygon mode,'

[11:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'you can see there\'s not much polygons to do some operations. That\'s totally fine because here in blender, there is remesh. All you need is to come up with the right voxel size and it will sort of recalculate the mesh.'

[11:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'And then it will be easier to work with the mesh. Okay. If you want more details, just get the resolution lower, but don\'t go too low because it can freeze your computer. If you try to recalculate it into millions'

[11:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'of polygons. And the last thing I want to show you is how to create connectors manually, just in case you need it. And so you see how much time we save using item. We\'re going to need to create box and'

[11:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'the top part, we\'re going to scale it a little bit. Now it looks like a connector. Again, this size is up to you to select the right size that you think is more suitable.'

[12:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'What we\'re going to need to do is to press control a and apply rotation and scale. That\'s going to be needed because we\'re going to use Boolean operations. And now we\'re going to need to place it in the right position. The trick here will'

[12:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'be to create a duplicate of the same cube later and scale it a little bit. So the bigger cube basically will be a hole and the smaller cube will be a plug. And now we\'re going'

[12:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'to need to add modifier called Boolean. So for the smaller cube, we\'re going to use a Boolean with a union and join it with the base. So it actually makes one object right now. And for the bigger cube, we\'re going to'

[12:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'choose difference. Now, when we disabled the cube, we can see that there is a hole and don\'t forget to apply the Boolean modifier. So it\'s baked into the mesh. Well, pretty much that\'s it. Now we have connector. If you want to'

[12:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
